            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#RW">
                <p>Sacred to the spirits of the dead. Abdalas (slave) of Domitia (wife) of Domitian, head shepherd of the sheep, who lived well in his position, for eighty years.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>A parallel funerary inscription for Chius, magnus magister pecoris has now been found some 16km to the northwest (<ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001693">ISic001693</ref>)</p>
            </div>
